{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"simplified"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Number","preciseIdentifier":"s:9XestiMath6NumberV","identifier":"doc:\/\/XestiMath\/documentation\/XestiMath\/Number"},{"kind":"text","text":" { "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If this number is already in the simplest internal representation, then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this number itself is returned."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A number may be represented internally by a variety of data structures."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, there are different data structures for representing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“large” and “small” exact integers, exact fractions, floating-point"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values, and complex numbers. Performing a numeric operation may result"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in a number with a representation containing extraneous information."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, the  numbers "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"5\/4"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"3\/4"},{"type":"text","text":" are represented internally by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"data structures that contain the numerator and denominator of each"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"number. (Something like, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{ numerator: 5, denominator: 4 }"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{ numerator: 3, denominator: 4 }"},{"type":"text","text":", respectively.) Adding those numbers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"together results in the number "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2"},{"type":"text","text":". However, for efficiency, that result"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is also represented internally by a data structure that contains "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"both","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a numerator "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" a denominator. (Something like, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{ numerator: 2, denominator: 1 }"},{"type":"text","text":".) In this case, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"simplified"},{"type":"text","text":" property would"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the internal representation to contain "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"only","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the (exact)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"integer result."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"title":"simplified","modules":[{"name":"XestiMath"}],"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"simplified","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:9XestiMath6NumberV","text":"Number","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"extendedModule":"XestiMath","roleHeading":"Instance Property","symbolKind":"property","externalID":"s:9XestiMath6NumberV10simplifiedACvp","role":"symbol"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/XestiMath\/documentation\/XestiMath","doc:\/\/XestiMath\/documentation\/XestiMath\/Number"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/XestiMath\/documentation\/XestiMath\/Number\/simplified","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/xestimath\/number\/simplified"]}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The simplest internal representation of this number."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://XestiMath/documentation/XestiMath":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Math tools."}],"title":"XestiMath","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/xestimath","identifier":"doc:\/\/XestiMath\/documentation\/XestiMath","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://XestiMath/documentation/XestiMath/Number/simplified":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"simplified","identifier":"doc:\/\/XestiMath\/documentation\/XestiMath\/Number\/simplified","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"simplified"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:9XestiMath6NumberV","text":"Number"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The simplest internal representation of this number."}],"url":"\/documentation\/xestimath\/number\/simplified"},"doc://XestiMath/documentation/XestiMath/Number":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Number","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A generalized numeric value that supports a “number tower” patterned after","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that in the Scheme programming language.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/XestiMath\/documentation\/XestiMath\/Number","url":"\/documentation\/xestimath\/number","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Number"}],"title":"Number","role":"symbol"}}}